Business Brief -- Philadelphia Electric Co.:
   Electric Bills Will Drop 7%;
   Lower Taxes Cited in Part
Joseph F. Paquette Jr., chairman and chief executive
officer, said the decreases will save the company's 1.5
million customers about $236 million a year, or about $5 on
an average monthly residential bill. He said the decreases
won't affect per-share earnings for the company's
stockholders.
   The Limerick station has two units; the first was built in
1986, and the second was completed in 1990. The company was
allowed to increase rates for a fixed number of years to
recover its capital investment in the units.